text.tspan: Fertility rate vs. GDP per capita, 2023

The
total fertility rate
summarizes the total number of births a woman would have, if she experienced the birth
rates seen in women of each age group in one particular year across her childbearing years. This is shown
against gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, adjusted for inflation and differences in living costs between
GDP per capita (international-$ in 2021 prices; plotted on a logarithmic axis)
Births per woman (live births per woman; plotted on a logarithmic axis)
Data source: UN, World Population Prospects (2024); Feenstra et al. - Penn World Table (2025)

Note: GDP per capita is expressed in
international-$
at 2021 prices, using multiple benchmark years to adjust for differences in living costs
